CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 20, 1959, pg. A9, reads: "Burning Mortgage The mortgage on St. Alphaeus Temple, United Holy Church of America, 502 N. Aiken Ave., was burned recently amidst impressive ceremony.  Among those who officiated were the pastor, the Rev. James C. Colburn, Deacon Hosten, craftsman Cleveland Davis, Earl D. Johnson, A.W. Welch, and juvenile members Brenda, Edward and Joyce Franklin. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group of women, men, some wearing Masonic collars and aprons, including Rev. James C. Colburn, Deacon Hosten, Cleveland Davis, Earl D. Johnson, and A.W. Welch, and children Brenda Franklin, Edward Franklin, and Joyce Franklin, gathered for mortgage burning ceremony in St. Alphaeus Temple, United Holy Church of America, 502 N. Aiken Avenue, third version
